div.p:
3. This is very important. Substitutions should not be made for our Sacrament Meetings.
Seminary graduation exercises should be held at some other hour or on some weekday night;
they should not take the place of our Sacrament Meetings.

"The teacher's duty is to watch over the church always, and be with and strengthen them;

"And see that there is no iniquity in the church, neither hardness with each other, neither
lying, backbiting, nor evil speaking;

"And see that the church meet together often, and also see that all the members do their
duty" (D&C 20:53-55).
